abstract: Congressional Budget Office expects federal deficit to fall to $426 billion in 2015, $60 billion less than it expected in March, but analysts warn that current debt path is 'unsustainable.'
lead_paragraph: The federal deficit is down, but in a report analysts warned that high shortfalls will return unless lawmakers act.

headline.main: Federal Deficit Dips, but Report Shows ‘Unsustainable Path’
headline.print_headline: Federal Deficit Dips but Report Shows ‘Unsustainable Path’
